==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Service uniform
<hw>Service uniform</hw>. <fld>(Mil. & Nav.)</fld> <def>The uniform
prescribed in regulations for active or routine service, in distinction
from dress, full dress, etc. In the United States army it is of
olive-drab woolen or khaki-colored cotton, with all metal attachments of
dull-finish bronze, with the exceptional of insignia of rank, which are
of gold or silver finish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Servient</ent>⟦br⟧
